-	Baseline Needs Assessment conducted and needs for IT equipment identified to be provided to the Nukus Public services centers. Business process re-engineering was carried in regards to the public services related to “a birth of child” (issuance of birth registration, payment of social allowance, registering at a local policlinic etc.) and “retirement” (applying for a state pension). Draft administrative regulations have been prepared for a “joined-up”, accessible, affordable public services, which will significantly reduce time and efforts to receive the services. “Joining-up” services will also make receiving different services from different agencies in one place filling out one document possible. The data will be shared with different agencies;
-	The Council of Ministers of Karakalpakstan and the Agency for Public Services have proposed to equip the Nukus city and Kungrad district Public services centers (PSC). Nukus city PSC serves the biggest number of clients (serving around 1000 clients per day), while Kungrad district is the largest district in Uzbekistan, covering almost 10% of the country’s area. The needed IT equipment were procured and provided to the Nukus Public service center that enhanced the efficiency of the provided services;
